## Design Philosophy

CipherSwarm's frontend is:
- Minimalist and functional
- Server-rendered (no SPA)
- Progressive enhancement over raw HTML using HTMX. See [htmx-guidelines.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/code/htmx-guidelines.mdc)

## Component System

- Use **Flowbite** for accessible, Tailwind-compatible UI components (modals, alerts, dropdowns, tabs, pagination, etc.).
- Use **Tailwind CSS** utility classes for layout and spacing.
- Use **HTMX** for dynamic interaction (e.g., inline updates, modals, forms).

## UX Guidelines for Cursor

- Always prefer progressive enhancement: base experience should work without JS.
- Use HTMX for:
  - Inline editing (`hx-get` to show form, `hx-post` to submit)
  - Modal loading (`hx-target="#modal"`, `hx-swap="innerHTML"`)
  - Pagination (`hx-push-url`, `hx-get`, replace content area)

## Cursor Examples

```html
<!-- Button that triggers an HTMX modal load -->
<button hx-get="/agents/new" hx-target="#modal" hx-swap="innerHTML" class="btn btn-primary">
  Add Agent
</button>
```

```html
<!-- Form returned in response to hx-get -->
<form hx-post="/agents" hx-target="#modal" hx-swap="none" class="space-y-4">
  <input type="text" name="name" class="input" placeholder="Agent Name" required />
  <button type="submit" class="btn btn-success">Create</button>
</form>
```

## Tailwind Tips

- Use `space-y-*`, `p-*`, and `text-*` for consistent spacing and typography.
- Prefer `grid` or `flex` layout helpers over manual CSS.
- Use Flowbite’s modal structure or tabs where appropriate.

## Cursor DON'Ts

- Don't write raw JavaScript unless absolutely required.
- Don't use React or any SPA/JSX tooling — this is not a SPA.
- Don't override Tailwind classes with custom CSS unless unavoidable.

Keep it clean, responsive, and server-driven.



### Accessibility and Component Hygiene

- All modals and alerts must use `aria-*` attributes correctly.
- All interactive components must be accessible via keyboard navigation.
- Do not rely on Tailwind plugins or external CDNs — keep all styling inline and local.
